oc:kn_03d4e974 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any chart or visualization" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Keep visualizations simple — one main message per chart. Label clearly with title, axes, and legend." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Overloaded charts confuse rather than clarify; simplicity drives comprehension" .

oc:kn_58a3eeee a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before beginning any analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify file format is xlsx, csv, or xls. Confirm file is readable and not password-protected. Check for data quality issues (missing values, duplicates) before analysis." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Invalid input files or poor data quality will produce unreliable results" .

oc:kn_88d888fb a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating insights and recommendations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always consider industry benchmarks, seasonality, and external context when interpreting data patterns." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Data without context can lead to incorrect business decisions" .

oc:kn_a0d30aff a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before performing any statistical analysis or visualization" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never skip data cleaning before analysis. Always handle missing values, remove duplicates, and verify data types first." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Dirty data leads to misleading insights and incorrect conclusions" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b333c25e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When starting any data analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Clean data first (handle missing values, duplicates) 2. Define metrics clearly 3. Perform exploratory analysis 4. Consider context (benchmarks, seasonality) 5. Validate findings by cross-checking sources" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Following a structured process prevents flawed conclusions from dirty or misunderstood data" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_b64cc6cf a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When working with very large, complex, or scanned datasets" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Large datasets may require sampling. Complex statistical models need specialized tools. Cannot guarantee 100% accuracy on OCR'd data." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Memory and processing limitations constrain what can be analyzed in-situ" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_d12b4d5a a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When recommending or creating visualizations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Choose chart type based on data relationship: Line for trends over time, Pie/Donut for part-of-whole, Bar for comparison, Histogram for distribution, Scatter for correlation, Map for geographic data." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Wrong chart type obscures the message; matching chart to data relationship maximizes clarity" .

